Ri referred to a joint statement issued by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first summit between a sitting U.S. president and a North Korean leader in Singapore on June 12, where Kim promised to work towards "dealing nuclear weapons on the Korean peninsula" while Trump promised guarantees for North Korea's security.
North Korea has sought a formal end to the 1950-53 Korean War, but the U.S. has said Pyongyang must first dismantle its nuclear weapons.
Washington has also declined negotiations to ease tough international sanctions on North Korea.
