He stresses the importance of searching for bats before performing maintenance in real estate, as it is possible that accidental destruction of a single dwelling could kill up to 400 females and young, and possibly wipe out an entire population.
Flatter mice are peaceful and it is illegal to kill, trouble or disturb them or destroy their bones.
Elisabeth Ferrell, a Scottish officer for the Bat Conservation Trust, has encouraged the public to help.
She said: “We still have a lot to learn about our bats and for many of our species we don’t know how their populations feel.”
