Algae bloom: Halter decreases in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest report from the Florida Fisheries and Wildlife Commission shows a general decrease in concentrations of algae blooms for parts of the area around Tampa Bay.
According to the Commission, more uneven blooms are reported in the areas around the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier, which may indicate a decrease in holdings.
The algal bloom extends over 20 miles off the coast, from northern Pinellas to southern Lee.
Spots can be seen about one and a half miles out into the sea outside the municipality of Hillsborough, but in fewer places compared to last week.
Algae blooming has also been observed in the municipality of Pasco.
